ry to find love and meaning in lives marked by structural violence, social marginalization, drug addiction, and HIV/AIDS. Linking the political economy of inequalities along the border with emotional lived experience, this book explores how intimate relationships become dangerous safe havens that fundamentally shape both partners' well-being. Through these stories, we are urged to reimagine the socially transformative power of love to carve new pathways to health equity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aProstituteszMexicozTijuana (Baja California)xSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishz978311099395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2022z9783110994186oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520384408zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520384408zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520384408/original  a978-3-11-076649-3 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099395-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-SEWb2